The most common bug to avoid when implementing the longest increasing subsequence function is incorrectly initializing or updating the dynamic programming table, which can lead to incorrect results. 

```python
def longest_increasing_subseq(xs):
    if not xs:
        return 0
    dp = [1] * len(xs)
    for i in range(1, len(xs)):
        for j in range(i):
            if xs[i] > xs[j]:
                dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1)
    return max(dp)
```
